t .frac .num,.mw-parser-output .frac .den{font-size:80%;line-height:0;vertical-align:super}.mw-parser-output .frac .den{vertical-align:sub}.mw-parser-output .sr-only{border:0;clip:rect(0,0,0,0);clip-path:polygon(0px 0px,0px 0px,0px 0px);height:1px;margin:-1px;overflow:hidden;padding:0;position:absolute;width:1px}7+1⁄2-mile-long (12.1 km) road is located between Old Winter Beach Road and the current A1A, along the western side of Orchid Island, and is unpaved. It is part of the Indian River Lagoon Scenic Highway system, and the southernmost road in the highway system. Part of the trail goes through the Pelican Island National Wildlife Refuge."],"sourceSection":"History","src":"wikipedia"},"highlights":[{"n":"Hillsboro Inlet","d":"Crosses Hillsboro Inlet Bridge","q":"Hillsboro Inlet","lat":26.25976389,"lng":-80.08260833,"src":"wikipedia"},{"n":"Lake Worth Beach","d":"Crosses To Lake Worth Bridge","q":"Lake Worth Beach","lat":26.62666667,"lng":-80.05888889,"src":"wikipedia"},{"n":"West Palm Beach","d":"Junction toward Flagler Drive","q":"West Palm Beach","lat":26.74694444,"lng":-80.13111111,"src":"wikipedia"},{"n":"Fort Pierce","d":"Crosses Indian River","q":"Fort Pierce","lat":27.40416667,"lng":-80.39111111,"src":"wikipedia"}],"references":[{"n":1,"text":"FDOT straight line diagrams Archived March 6, 2014, at the Wayback Machine, accessed December 2013","url":"http://www2.dot.state.fl.us/Straight-linesOnlineGIS/"},{"n":2,"text":"\"A1A Scenic & Historic Coastal Byway\". America's Byways. Federal Highway Administration. Retrieved December 14, 2022.","url":"https://fhwaapps.fhwa.dot.gov/bywaysp/StateMaps/Show/byway/2477"},{"n":3,"text":"\"A1A Scenic & Historic Coastal Byway\". Scenic A1A. Friends of A1A Scenic & Historic Coastal Byway. Retrieved December 24, 2014.","url":"http://www.scenica1a.org/"},{"n":4,"text":"\"FDOT State Roads TDA\". Florida Department of Transportation. May 24, 2026. Archived from the original on May 25, 2026. Retrieved May 25, 2026.","url":"https